Implemented automatic one-time retry in [ActiveProjectService.java](C:/Users/james/IdeaProjects/ralphy/src/main/java/net/uberfoo/ai/ralphy/ActiveProjectService.java). A failed story now gets one immediate second attempt with a fresh run ID and persisted queued/running/finalized state; if that retry also fails, the run stops, the story remains `FAILED`, and it stays resumable later through the existing retry flow after reopen. I added coverage in [ActiveProjectServiceTest.java](C:/Users/james/IdeaProjects/ralphy/src/test/java/net/uberfoo/ai/ralphy/ActiveProjectServiceTest.java) and [AppShellUiTest.java](C:/Users/james/IdeaProjects/ralphy/src/test/java/net/uberfoo/ai/ralphy/AppShellUiTest.java), updated [windows-smoke-checklist.md](C:/Users/james/IdeaProjects/ralphy/docs/windows-smoke-checklist.md), and appended the required entry in [progress.md](C:/Users/james/IdeaProjects/ralphy/.ralph-tui/progress.md).

